ld competition began Aug. 1 and will end Aug. 11.The last event contested will be the women's marathon, which will begin Sunday at 1 a.m. Eastern.\", \"from\": 731, \"to\": 894, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Looking ahead to the much-anticipated 4x100 relays, both Team USA squads will have the opportunity to add to their dominance in the discipline, though it will mean regaining their footing after a few off years.\", \"from\": 896, \"to\": 1106, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 953, \"end\": 961, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.9991157660578632, \"rank\": 0.0008850164863109173, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read more:When Are The 4x100 Relay Finals At The 2024 Olympics?\", \"from\": 1108, \"to\": 1171, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What To Know  Quincy Hall already snagged the gold medal for the United States in the men's 400, and Alexis Holmes will have the chance to make it a sweep for Team USA after taking one of two automatic spots during her semifinal heat Wednesday (50.00).\", \"from\": 1172, \"to\": 1424, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1186, \"end\": 1192, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quincy_Center_station\", \"score\": 0.9999151967643605, \"rank\": 6.230525640006815e-05, \"text\": \"Quincy\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quincy_Center_station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quincy_Center_station\"}, {\"begin\": 1237, \"end\": 1250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999984246031676, \"rank\": 6.694194937941983e-07, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1280, \"end\": 1286, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\", \"score\": 0.9996819261747254, \"rank\": 0.0003181750283059556, \"text\": \"Holmes\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\"}, {\"begin\": 1331, \"end\": 1339, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.9991157660578632, \"rank\": 0.0008850164863109173, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Holmes finished behind the Dominican Republic's Marileidy Paulino (49.21).\", \"from\": 1426, \"to\": 1500, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1426, \"end\": 1432, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\", \"score\": 0.9996819261747254, \"rank\": 0.0003181750283059556, \"text\": \"Holmes\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\"}, {\"begin\": 1453, \"end\": 1471, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dominican_Republic_national_baseball_team\", \"score\": 0.9838915046224962, \"rank\": 0.016372168463809053, \"text\": \"Dominican Republic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dominican_Republic_national_baseball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dominican_Republic_national_baseball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1474, \"end\": 1491, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marileidy_Paulino\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marileidy Paulino\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marileidy_Paulino\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marileidy_Paulino\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paulino was second among all qualifiers, while Holmes was seventh.\", \"from\": 1501, \"to\": 1567, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1548, \"end\": 1554, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\", \"score\": 0.9996819261747254, \"rank\": 0.0003181750283059556, \"text\": \"Holmes\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sherlock_Holmes\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Bahrain's Salwa Eid Naser was the fastest in the semifinals at 49.08.\", \"from\": 1568, \"to\": 1637, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1568, \"end\": 1575, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bahrain_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9737171238322965, \"rank\": 0.026984007485724448, \"text\": \"Bahrain\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bahrain_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bahrain_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1578, \"end\": 1593, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salwa_Eid_Naser\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Salwa Eid Naser\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salwa_Eid_Naser\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Salwa_Eid_Naser\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Shaunae Miller-Uibo of the Bahamas won the women's 400 in 2016 and 2020, but she did not make the semifinals this year.\", \"from\": 1639, \"to\": 1758, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1639, \"end\": 1658, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaunae_Miller-Uibo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Shaunae Miller-Uibo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaunae_Miller-Uibo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Shaunae_Miller-Uibo\"}, {\"begin\": 1666, \"end\": 1673, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Bahamas\", \"score\": 0.9999998331036434, \"rank\": 1.5130432090121842e-07, \"text\": \"Bahamas\", \"types\": [\"Q6